When to Use Comparable:

1)Use comparable when there is a single ,default sorting order that makes sense for the class(e.g sorting employee by ID or names alphabatically)

2)Good for models where the "natural order" is unlikely to change

When to use Comparator

1)Use Comparator when you need multiple sorting sequences for the same object (e.g., sorting products by price, name, or rating).

2)Ideal when you don’t want to modify the model class to introduce sorting logic.

3)Use Comparator with lambdas for a concise, inline sorting definition.


